      Perhaps a majority of folks who are familar with the U.S (misnamed) Intelligence Community suspect that probably 90 per cent of useful intelligence is readily available from open sources. Of course the 'friction' of using open sources is separating the wheat (verifiable information) from the chaff (unvarifiable information). An open sources agency is a good idea, but would require a world class information management system.

                  
